IMPRESSION:  This is an abnormal video EEG due to:  1. Occasional mild excess of theta in wakefulness 2. Episodes of body rocking captured described above, without associated ictal change in cerebral rhythms, most consistent with nonepileptic behavioral events. For some of these events, the patient reported her typical habitual semiology of "lights flashing" preceding the onset of shaking. For most, however, she was unable to remember her symptoms when questioned afterwards. 3. Episodes involving hearing ringing/buzzing in left ear do not involve change in cerebral rhythms and are of unclear etiology.   FINAL
